5000|$|Tom was {{mentioned}} by James Field in 1611 in Coryat's Crudities: [...] "Tom Thumbe is dumbe, until the pudding <b>creepe,</b> {{in which he}} was intomb'd, then out doth peepe." [...] The incident of the pudding was the most popular in connection with the character. It is alluded to in Ben Johnson's masque of the Fortunate Isles: [...] "Thomas Thumb in a pudding fat, with Doctor Rat." ...|$|E

